Doreen Lang [MM ‘02] was recently appointed executive director of Bridges by EPOCH Memory Care Assisted Living at Hingham. In her role as executive director, Lang will oversee all operational aspects of the community, including its programs, care and services. Lang will also focus on providing ongoing education and support to staff and families. With 15 years' experience in property and sales management, Lang has held such roles as senior regional manager and vice president of Property Management in senior living communities. Prior to joining Bridges by EPOCH, Lang served as a general manager of operations. She is also an accomplished author and past speaker for the Mass-ALA annual conference....

A new partnership between Cambridge College, Mel King Institute for Community Building, and Massachusetts Growth Capital Corporation (MGCC) has formed an innovative program that will educate small business development officers throughout the Commonwealth. The program will help accelerate the start up and growth of small businesses from under-invested communities served by MGCC. The partners will offer the first cycle of this program starting in January 2020 to professionals that work at community development corporations, community development finance institutes and other non-profit community-based organizations that help entrepreneurs start and grow small businesses. These non-profit organizations focus specifically on businesses led by people of color, immigrants and women as well as businesses located in lower income urban and rural areas.

Thank you for your interest in Cambridge College. At Cambridge College, we welcome capable, motivated individuals who are committed to changing their lives, work places, and communities for the better. We don't ask for standardized exam scores. We respect our students’ diverse skills and experiences and leverage their real-world experience in the classroom.

By connecting what happens in class with what happens in your life and workplace, Cambridge College provides an academically stimulating and personally relevant education that will make you better prepared for the life you choose.

Cambridge College believes that educational opportunity is a cornerstone of the American dream, and that we have an obligation to unlock educational opportunities for a greater number of people. Towards this end, we are committed to keeping our tuition costs low and to providing financial aid to those who qualify. Visit our financial aid page for more information on the types of financial assistance, scholarships, loans, and work-study programs we offer.
To apply to Cambridge College, follow these steps.
. To find the program of study that best supports your academic and career goals, use our Program Finder Tool and/or talk to one of our Admissions Counselors in your region 1-800-829-4723.

. While all of our programs require an application, application fee, transcripts, and letters of recommendation, some programs require additional information regarding past academic and work experience. Read and make note of the specific admissions requirements for your program and school.
